When Cursor auto-generates a Git commit message for this repository (Source Control sparkle button), follow these rules strictly:

Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>

- type: English — feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, revert
- scope: optional — monolith, gateway, blog, user, rpg, ent, wire, ws, config, deploy
- subject: Simplified Chinese (简体中文) only, no period, max 50 characters
- First line is subject only; put details in body as bullet list if needed
- Never use English subject (e.g. "Add initial implementation", "Update code")
- Forbidden: WIP, subject without type

Examples:
chore: 初始化 Hertz 单体脚手架与 wire 装配
feat(auth): 实现 JWT 登录与 bcrypt 密码兼容
fix(article): 修复列表分页未过滤软删除
docs: 添加 blog-server-go 架构与分阶段实施规划文档

For NestJS migration commits, mention the corresponding Nest module in body when relevant.
